'''Ankit Bathla''' (born 10 October 1988 in New Delhi, India) is an [[India]]n [[television actor]] known for his portrayal of Madhav in ''[[Beta Hi Chahiye]]'', Dhruv Pandey in ''[[Thapki Pyar Ki]]'' and Akshay Khanna in ''[[Tu Sooraj Main Saanjh, Piyaji]]''. He was last seen playing Rajat in ''[[Naagin (2015 TV series)|Naagin: Bhagya Ka Zehreela Khel]]''.

==ᱱᱤᱡᱮᱨ ᱡᱤᱭᱚᱱ==
Ankit Bathla was born on 10 October 1988 to mother Mugdha Bathla and father Anil Kumar Bathla in [[New Delhi]], [[India]]. He completed his schooling from   [[St. Mark's Senior Secondary Public School]], [[Meera Bagh]], [[Delhi]]. He later completed his graduation in Economics (Hons) from [[Sri Guru Gobind Singh College of Commerce]] of [[Delhi University]].<ref name="BathlaBio">{{cite web|title=Ankit Bathla LinkedIn Profile|url=https://www.linkedin.com/profile/view?id=231635612&authType=NAME_SEARCH&authToken=xM0K&locale=en_US&srchid=1605453651430948007764&srchindex=10&srchtotal=15&trk=vsrp_people_res_name&trkInfo=VSRPsearchId%3A1605453651430948007764%2CVSRPtargetId%3A231635612%2CVSRPcmpt%3Aprimary%2CVSRPnm%3Atrue|website=LinkedIn.com|publisher=LinkedIn|accessdate=6 May 2015}}</ref>

==ᱠᱟ.ᱢᱤ ᱡᱤᱭᱚᱱ==
Ankit Bathla<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/hindi/i-just-love-coming-to-lucknow-tv-actor-ankit-bathla/articleshow/72415959.cms|title=I just love coming to Lucknow: TV actor Ankit Bathla|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=2019-12-24}}</ref> began working as a trainer with [[American Express]] before moving into acting.<ref name="AnkitBathla">{{cite web|title=Ankit Bathla|url=http://www.tellychakkar.com/celebs/tv/ankit-bathla|website=tellychakkar.com|publisher=TellyChakkar|accessdate=6 May 2015}}</ref> His first television appearance was on [[DD National]] in ''Sammaan Ek Adhikaar'' where he played an anti-hero. Later he acted in ''[[Bhagonwali-Baante Apni Taqdeer]]'', playing the pivotal character Abhigyan on [[Zee TV]], followed by ''[[Mata Ki Chowki]]'' as Arjun on [[Sahara One]], and ''Hamari Saass Leela'' as the youngest son, Ayush, of Leela Parekh ([[Apara Mehta]]) on [[Colors (TV channel)|Colors]].

In 2010 he played the role of Gaurav in ''Hum''<ref name="BathlaBio"/> on [[DD National]] opposite [[Mona Vasu]]. Later he acted in ''Haar Jeet (TV series)''<ref name="BathlaBio"/> as Abhigyan on [[Imagine TV]]. In 2013, Ankit worked on the TV show ''[[Beta Hi Chahiye]]'' as Madhav on [[Big Magic]] opposite [[Garima Tiwari]]; it was the first daily soap opera launched on [[BIG Magic]] by [[Reliance Entertainment]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Big Magic Launches Beta Hi Chahiye|url=http://www.indiantelevision.com/headlines/y2k13/may/may107.php|website=indiantelevision.com|publisher=Indian Television|accessdate=7 May 2015}}</ref>
After ''[[Beta Hi Chahiye]]'', Ankit played the role of Karan Khanna who was the love interest of Veera ([[Digangana Suryavanshi]]) in ''[[Ek Veer Ki Ardaas...Veera]]'' on [[Star Plus]]. In the fifth episode of ''[[Love by Chance (Indian TV series)|Love by Chance]]'' (airing on [[Bindass]]) he played the role of [[Lieutenant colonel]] Kanishka Mehta.

In November 2014, Bathla joined the cast of the show [[Ajab Gajab Ghar Jamai]] (Red Dot Productions) on [[Big Magic]] playing the role of Krishna.<ref>{{cite web|title= Ankit Bathla in Big Magic’s Ajab Gajab Ghar Jamai|url= http://www.tellychakkar.com/tv/tv-news/ankit-bathla-big-magic-s-ajab-gajab-ghar-jamai-141108|website=tellychakkar.com|publisher=tellychakkar|accessdate=7 May 2015}}</ref>

In March 2015, Bathla appeared in an episode of Red Dot Productions's show [[Halla Bol]] on [[Bindass]].<ref>{{cite web|title= Ankit Bathla to feature in Bindass' Halla Bol|url= http://www.tellychakkar.com/tv/tv-news/ankit-bathla-feature-bindass-halla-bol-150316|website=tellychakkar.com|publisher=tellychakkar|accessdate=7 May 2015}}</ref> He appeared in [[Sony TV|Sony Entertainment Television]]'s mythological show [[Sankatmochan Mahabali Hanuman]] which premiered on 4 May 2015.<ref>{{cite web|title=Sony TV's Hanumaan gets its launch date|url=http://www.tellychakkar.com/tv/tv-news/sony-tvs-hanumaan-gets-its-launch-date-150331|website=tellychakkar.com|publisher=tellychakkar|accessdate=7 May 2015}}</ref>
Currently Ankit is part of serial [[Thapki Pyar Ki]] on [[Colors (TV channel)|Colors]].In [[Thapki Pyar Ki]] Ankit is essaying the lead role of Dhruv who is an owner of a news channel and makes serious faces.
In September 2016, Ankit hosted Benadryl Big Golden Voice Season 4 Finale in Mumbai.
In May 2017, he appeared in an Indonesian Series Cinta Di Pangkuan Himalaya on [[antv]].
On 17 March 2018, he played in a web series Love, lust and confusion by VIU India starring Tara Alisha Berry
<ref>{{cite web|title= Ankit Bathla of Thapki Pyar Ki to be seen in an Indonesian Series |url= http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/hindi/Ankit-Bathla-of-Thapki-Pyar-Ki-to-be-seen-in-an-Indonesian-Series/articleshow/58111330.cms|work=The Times of India|accessdate=10 April 2017}}</ref>

